content:
TransactedChangeCallback Delegate

Definition

A delegate that refers to a method in a custom DesignerActionList object that is to be called by the stem.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.InvokeTransactedChange* method for implementing property changes in the designer's associated control.

In this Article

public delegate bool TransactedChangeCallback(object context);
Inheritance
Object
Delegate
TransactedChangeCallback

Examples

For a code example, see InvokeTransactedChange.
